    "innovation_research_20260413": {
      "type": "research",
      "category": "ai_agent_innovation",
      "facts": [
        {
          "content": "## arXiv: When Agent Markets Arrive\nAI agents are increasingly transacting on behalf of users -- delegating tasks, spending budgets, and negotiating with unfamiliar counterparties. From skill marketplaces to agent-only bazaars, the econ\n\n## arXiv: Reimagining RAN Automation in 6G: An Agentic AI Framework with Hierarchical Onli\nIn this paper, we propose an Agentic Artificial Intelligence (AI) framework for wireless networks. The framework coordinates a pool of AI agents guided by Natural Language (NL) inputs from a human ope\n\n## arXiv: Networking-Aware Energy Efficiency in Agentic AI Inference: A Survey\nThe rapid emergence of Large Language Models (LLMs) has catalyzed Agentic artificial intelligence (AI), autonomous systems integrating perception, reasoning, and action into closed-loop pipelines for \n\n## arXiv: PRIME: Training Free Proactive Reasoning via Iterative Memory Evolution for User\nThe development of autonomous tool-use agents for complex, long-horizon tasks in collaboration with human users has become the frontier of agentic research. During multi-turn Human-AI interactions, th\n\n## arXiv: SWE-Adept: An LLM-Based Agentic Framework for Deep Codebase Analysis and Structu\nLarge language models (LLMs) exhibit strong performance on self-contained programming tasks. However, they still struggle with repository-level software engineering (SWE), which demands (1) deep codeb\n\n## arXiv: Structured Prompt Language: Declarative Context Management for LLMs\nWe present SPL (Structured Prompt Language), a declarative SQL-inspired language that treats large language models as generative knowledge bases and their context windows as constrained resources. SPL\n\n## HN: How TRM Labs Scaled Security with Self-Improving AI Vulnerability Agents\nURL: https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/scaling-security-in-the-age-of-ai-how-trm-labs-built-self-improving-vulnerability-agents-with-reinforcement-learning\n\n## HN: Hermes Agent: The self-improving AI agent\nURL: https://github.com/NousRes...",
          "confidence": 0.8,
          "extracted_at": "2026-04-13T19:03:51.819161",
          "category": "innovation_research"
        }
      ],
      "priority": "MEDIUM",
      "created": "2026-04-13T19:03:51.819181",
      "tags": [
        "innovation",
        "research",
        "ai_agent",
        "2026",
