    "innovation_research_20260418": {
      "type": "research",
      "category": "ai_agent_innovation",
      "facts": [
        {
          "content": "## arXiv: Self-adaptive Multi-Access Edge Architectures: A Robotics Case\nThe growth of compute-intensive AI tasks highlights the need to mitigate the processing costs and improve performance and energy efficiency. This necessitates the integration of intelligent agents as \n\n## arXiv: ArtiCAD: Articulated CAD Assembly Design via Multi-Agent Code Generation\nParametric Computer-Aided Design (CAD) of articulated assemblies is essential for product development, yet generating these multi-part, movable models from high-level descriptions remains unexplored. \n\n## arXiv: Towards Personalizing Secure Programming Education with LLM-Injected Vulnerabili\nAccording to constructivist theory, students learn software security more effectively when examples are grounded in their own code. Generic examples often fail to connect with students' prior work, li\n\n## arXiv: OOM-RL: Out-of-Money Reinforcement Learning Market-Driven Alignment for LLM-Base\nThe alignment of Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) for autonomous software engineering is constrained by evaluator epistemic uncertainty. Current paradigms, such as Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback \n\n## arXiv: Autonomous Evolution of EDA Tools: Multi-Agent Self-Evolved ABC\nThis paper introduces the first \\emph{self-evolving} logic synthesis framework, which leverages Large Language Model (LLM) agents to autonomously improve the source code of \\textsc{ABC}, the widely ad\n\n## arXiv: SWE-Adept: An LLM-Based Agentic Framework for Deep Codebase Analysis and Structu\nLarge language models (LLMs) exhibit strong performance on self-contained programming tasks. However, they still struggle with repository-level software engineering (SWE), which demands (1) deep codeb\n\n## HN: How TRM Labs Scaled Security with Self-Improving AI Vulnerability Agents\nURL: https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/scaling-security-in-the-age-of-ai-how-trm-labs-built-self-improving-vulnerability-agents-with-reinforcement-learning\n\n## HN: Hermes Agent: The self-improving AI ...",
          "confidence": 0.8,
          "extracted_at": "2026-04-18T09:26:17.587296",
          "category": "innovation_research"
        }
      ],
      "priority": "MEDIUM",
